							<a href="/web/20100826080148/http://www.bbc.com/travel/feature/20100723-wildlife-watching-in-costa-rica">
					<span class="summary">From the scarlet macaw to the elusive jaguar, Costa Rica offers unparalleled wildlife- and bird-watching. Visitors with a top pair of binoculars can find monkeys bounding through the treetops, sloths clinging to branches and toucans gliding beneath the canopy.</span>
